Komercni Banka AS (KOMB) , the Czech unit of
Societe Generale SA, gained in its biggest weekly advance this
quarter after European Central Bank President Mario Draghi
signaled yesterday the bank could do more to fight the regionâ€™s
debt crisis.  The stock surged 4.6 percent to 3,280 koruna at 4:24 p.m.
close in Prague, extending its rally this week to 7.5 percent.
It was the best performer today in the  PX (PX)  gauge of 14 companies,
which rose 1.7 percent.  Financial companies led a rally in European shares.  SocGen (GLE) 
rose 8.7 percent to a month high in Paris.  To contact the reporter on this story:
